					Dr.APJ Abdul kalam: Evergreen quotes from his speeches
	Dr Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul kalam was born on 15 october 1931, at Rameswaram in TamilNadu, India.
He specialized in Aeronautical Engineering from Madras Institue of Technology and become an eminent scientist.
Dr Kalam was awarded the Padma Bhushan(1981), the Padma Vibhshan(1990), and India's highest civilian award the 
Bharat Ratna in 1997. In 2002,Dr Kalam become the 11th President of India. He was fondly called the pepole's
President for being the first President in the country to connect with the youth via the internet.

	Named as the 'Missile Man' of India for his contributions in the field, he redefined the Presidency during
his tenure from 2002 to 2007. He often spoke to children and the country  youth-- inspiring them to think big in
life; he also penned a number of books. Dr kalam succumbed to a massive cardiac arrest and breath his last on july
27, 2015 while delivering a speech at IIM Shillong. Here are some of his evergreen quotes from his speeches.
